President Cyril Ramaphosa has conveyed his condolences to the United States following the passing of former President George H.W Bush. In A statementÂ Ramaphosa says the thoughts of the South African people are with the American people and in particular the Bush family in this time of mourning. The former American President passed away on Saturday at the age of 94. He served as the 41st President of the US from 1989 to 1993. 